content: Great app works just as well as my calculator does .
The takeout values for a 3" 45 degree elbow are wrong. The given value is 2" takeout, the actual takeout of a 3" 45 degree elbow is 1-7/8"
replyContent: Hello, I believe the type of elbow you are using is a factory cut long, and the calculator setting defaults to buttweld long.  Press [Conv] [Pipe Mat'l] to access the setting and continue pressing [Pipe Mat'l] until you see FC--L in the display.  Then enter 3 [INCH] [Pipe Size], 45 [Angle/Slope], then [Conv] [Angle/Slope]. TO should read 1 7/8 INCH

content: My calculator stop working the screen will Not display properly so I was forced to by the app I like it so far except that there is no backspace button For when I make a mistake on my input Is there any type of warranty on the calculator that I do not know about thank you O the app works great by the way
replyContent: Hi Andrew, for app backspace, swipe left to right across the display OR double-tap on the display.  1 swipe = 1 backspace, 1 double-tap = 1 backspace.  For the handheld calculator, please contact us at techsupport@calculated.com for warranty support.  Thank you for your support and kind words!

content: this this is hand in the pipeline biz. I just wish you could calculate degrees on 3r 90s.
replyContent: Thank you Nathan!  True, no support for 3R 90s.  However, we think you can simply multiply the T.O. by 2, using the built-in T.O. formula for BW-L 90's.  For example, 2" nominal, steel, BW-L elbow type, enter 90 into [Angle/Slope], 2 inch into [Pipe Size], then [Conv] [Angle/Slope] will give you a T.O. of 3"; multiply that by 2 for a 3R 90 T.O.
